Last night, a group of real ones trooped it to the birthplace to celebrate 50 years of hiphop music + culture. No bail was set and everyone made it home safe.

Run!!!

Fun story: In 1999, @RunDMC stopped by the @thesource office to preview their latest album #CrownRoyal. It wasn’t until they were leaving that it accured to me that I need them to sign SOMETHING. Ideally, a pair of shells. 🤔They started wrapping up, dapping staff, signaling they’re about to depart. I started doing the math: The nearest footlocker is a 20walk from office. Or, 10min if you a true Yorker. Fk that, this a 5min run (no punt). I’ll have 5 min to ask/pay for kix (if they have em) and another 3min if I go speed demon on em. I grabbed whatever size they had and booked it back as they’re getting into their limo. Sweaty like a mufucka 😅, but I got Run & JMJ #RIP to sign. Id take another 11+ years before I can eventually get @kingdmc to finalize my holy grail collectible. I waited on line at comic convention he was attending. (As life you have it, we ended up founding @dmcmakescomics 5 years later🙏🏽). For 8.11, I cracked open my other holy grail shells (Superstar1 anniversary) since it was the first time I’ve seen them perform since they signed my og pair. This was a ME thing, not to be advertised, but rather celebrated, by ME. So to walk in backstage and be asked by @bycestlazee if she can shoot them things on my feet, I happily obliged. The lesson here: patience + perseverance. When you REALLY want it, the intention + devotion drives the goal. The fulfillment is as priceless as the 3 signatures on the shoes. Thank you @adidasoriginals for the memory. It was worth the journey #MyAddidas
#JMJForever👑

This culture saved me. 

It’s done real good for me and my family in ways that I can’t even begin to describe. So “pardon me” if I remain protective of it. If I take too much pride in it. If I celebrate the smallest and biggest accomplishments associated with it. If 50 years of music + culture lives rent free in my head and it spills out in my vernacular. 

You wouldn’t understand. 

Happy 50th to greatest culture in music.

Must say, one of the best in recent memory. 

Our @dmcmakescomics panel celebrating 50 years of Comic Book influence on HipHop was a resounding success. Packed house, full capacity w/ a lil’ entry declined. Love to all the good folks through out both communities who pulled up to enjoy the discussion. 

Supreme level s/o to thee @RobMarkman , who moderated tf out of this wonderful panel like a reverend on a Sunday. 

This thing is powered by my patna, the 👑 @kingdmc who stated: 🗣️”Art succeeds where politics and religion fail.” 👏🏼👏🏽👏🏾👏🏾👏🏻👏🏿 His passion for the arts drives these moments that boom through out the chaotic corridors of @newyorkcomiccon and hits the ❤️ and minds of everyone he encounters, myself included. Honored (and still buggin😳) to call you a freind. 🫡

See ya’ll next year🦸🏽‍♂️🤖🦹🏽‍♂️👹🐲👻🚶🏽‍♂️…
